Text:
The Great Ize-athlon! Which this year once again
brings together those proud of their skills or
strength in order to win kagami rice cake!

The winner of the first contest, the "Great Ize
Fortune Dash," is the canine therianthrope Delta!
Yaaaaa!!!
Hehehe, yay, yay!

Delta, you're showing off. What do you intend to do
if your name gets out and it starts affecting your
missions?
Awoo! I'm really sorry...

I understand that you can play around at this shrine,
but we're here to get kagami rice cakes for Cid.

There are still two ascetic exercises to go! Everyone,
do your best to turn your luck around!
Now for our next contest!
Whoa! What's that? It's a white round thingy!
It looks like a pillar of rice cake, but...
It is our annual custom! The "Laughing Rice Cake!"

He is saying it like it's common knowledge again.
This event is only in its third year...

The rules are simple! You have to cut the rice cake
pillar into the shape of the Rice Cake Deity...while
blindfolded!

Rice Cake Deity? What's that? Do you know it,
Lady Alpha?

I want to say that I obviously don't, but...maybe
it's that thing over there. The statue next to the
priest.
It's plump. And so cute!

No, even if it's some kind of deity, don't call it
cute.

By the way, Rice Cake Deity goods are on sale at the
stall over there!
This shrine is really going to get cursed!

The time limit is 10 minutes. Let's see who can get
closest to the image of the Rice Cake Deity!

Later, we can all enjoy the deliciousness of the
statues you create!
Urk...this'll be hard. Seems kinda complicated.

You're great at breaking things but not so good at
making them.
But...I'll do my best! Blindfold me, please!
Go go go go go goooooo!
Umm... Maybe it'd be better if she stopped now?
Indeed.

Whew! Did I make the Rice Cake Deity? I'm sure a
miracle came outta these claws!
It's a shame, but miracles don't sell that cheap.
This is... Was it always a messed up rice cake?
The results are in! Delta's Rice Cake Deity gets...
Zero points!
Awoooooo!

Now the comments from the judging committee. "She has
desecrated art," "I saw something like this in a dream when
I was sick," and "Don't waste food."
Noooo...

That last comment sounds like a complete rejection of
the contest...

Currently, the participant Unkei has the highest
score at 98! Will there be a challenger who can
beat that score?!

I didn't even come close. I'll just cheer you on,
Lady Alpha.

So it's come to this. I will avenge you, Delta. I had
figured that this one was too much for you.

Surely, you know that your claws can't carve out the
plump form of the Rice Cake Deity.

Gah... But isn't it the same for you,  Lady Alpha?
Swords are only good for cutting straight...
Well, just watch. You there, please blindfold me.
Yes, just a moment.

Okay, the blindfold's on. How is it? Can you see how
many fingers I'm holding up?
Of course not. I'm blindfolded.
Haha, then it's okay!

Now to begin... But first, may I touch the real Rice
Cake Deity statue?
Yes, you may...

(I am not able to see it, but I can sense it... For
example, I could sense that therianthrope held
up three fingers just now.)

(Even without touching it, I can sense its shape to a
certain degree. You have no place in the Shadow
Garden if you can't even do that much.)

(I musn't use my eyes, but instead see with my heart.
Feel the shape of its soul... And strike.)

(So this is what you meant, Shadow. "Feel, do not
think" ...Now I understand).

Okay, I've finished. I want to start before I forget
anything.
R-Right, okay...start!
Yes!

(With the ferocity of fire and fluid elegance of water,
I pledge my blade to the Rice Cake Deity in my
mind's eye!)

Wow, amazing! I can see what you are doing, but I
can't do it like that!

(It's almost finished. As my heart desires, and as the
Rice Cake Deity's soul demands... My blade sings!)
Hah! Haaaaa!
I am finished.
Woooaaa!
Awoo! It looks exactly like the real thing!

The judging committee has voted! What score will
Alpha receive!?

100 points! There is no score higher! That makes it
the top score! The judges have no criticisms!
Wow, you did it! That's Lady Alpha for you!
Naturally.

But why'd you use a different sword move than usual?
You were so slow to carve it.

With so many eyes on us in public, if I were to use
Shadow Garden swordplay that might expose our
identities, wouldn't it?

This sword... Compared to my slime sword it is shaped
quite differently, so I adapted my swordplay to it, if that
makes sense.
Adapt...? I don't get it but okay!

All of the scores have been tallied! Alpha is ahead
with 100 points!

Well, I got a win and a loss! But I'll win in the
end!

(So far, so good...but is the kagami rice cake prize
really what Cid is after?)

(He will be disappointed if it is something completely
different.)

Alpha's statue is so impressive, we're going to put
it next to the kagami rice cake prize!

So that's kagami rice cake...it really is a mirror-
shaped rice cake. It's so big I would struggle to
hold it with my hands...

(It seems thinner than what Cid described, but it does
match his description of a mirror shape. I wonder if
he realizes how much trouble we are going through
to get it...)

Delta, whatever the last contest is, let's give it
our all.
Of course!
